WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:02.440
Well, good morning family.

00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:09.520
It's late night, almost early morning, but I thought I'd pray with you all for a little bit.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:18.160
We went to the Branson prayer conference and what a time we had.

00:00:18.160 --> 00:00:19.617
It was wonderful.

00:00:19.617 --> 00:00:21.074
How's my audio?

00:00:21.074 --> 00:00:24.636
Tell us in the comment section down below how the audio is.

00:00:24.636 --> 00:00:30.760
We're trying a new mic because it echoes a lot, so we're trying to make it so you can hear us better.

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:33.031
Let us know; if it's bad, we can switch back.

00:00:33.031 --> 00:00:35.818
I can push one button and it'll go back to the old one.

00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:39.560
If you don't like it, let us know.

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:44.297
But we went to the prayer conference in Branson and it was wonderful.

00:00:44.297 --> 00:00:52.960
I really enjoyed that with Sister Billie and the family and Lynn and so many other people.

00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:58.013
They came from all over the place and it was awesome to see everybody.

00:00:58.013 --> 00:01:05.060
At the tent meeting we prayed; it wasn't live, televised, or livestreamed.

00:01:08.693 --> 00:01:12.587
There were demonstrations and manifestations.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:25.340
Pastor Tracy Harris from Texarkana came and laid hands on everyone in the whole tent revival and the power of God was knocking people down.

00:01:25.340 --> 00:01:30.040
It was amazing to see people get so blessed.

00:01:30.040 --> 00:01:44.940
Then they had the fish fry, but I got to speak at that tent meeting and that was the first time I've ever spoken to that many people for that long.

00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:54.871
Usually I talk a little bit and I've done that several times, but this is the first time anyone has really handed me the mic and said 'go with it.

00:01:54.871 --> 00:02:04.320
' So it was a real blessing to be able to pray and do the things that the Lord allowed me to do during that service.

00:02:04.610 --> 00:02:07.451
I believe it went pretty well.

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:09.796
How can you judge your own thing?

00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:14.785
I just go by what they all said, and they said it was good.

00:02:14.785 --> 00:02:17.160
So I'm thankful for it.

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:49.280
But now we're home and I have an urgency in my spirit to pray for our economy, to keep praying against delays, coming against what I believe is the enemy trying to rear his head, trying to stop the blessing of what the Lord is wanting for this body.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:03:07.000
As I was driving around today, coming back into town and doing the things that the Lord wanted us to do, He said to me, 'Brandon, you're going to have to contend for what I've told you to do.

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:11.620
Don't just lay down and say, "whatever will be, will be.

00:03:11.620 --> 00:03:19.280
"' Like that song, 'Whatever will be, will be, Que sera, sera.

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:21.280
' It's not like that.

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:32.293
We have got to take our authority and we have got to start praying over what God has told us to do and not just sit there and say, 'Well, whatever will be, will be.

00:03:32.293 --> 00:03:35.340
' He said, 'Brandon, you're going to have to contend for it.

00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:39.560
You're going to have to fight for it, lay hold to it.

00:03:39.560 --> 00:03:48.520
' He said, 'Whenever I told the children of Israel to go and get the land, they had a choice.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:04:04.260
They could either say God is with us and who can be against us or have the attitude of a winner mentality, or you can shrink back and go, "well, we're the size of grasshoppers.

00:04:04.260 --> 00:04:08.293
"' The first generation did that and they died in the wilderness.

00:04:08.293 --> 00:04:17.079
But God had to raise up a whole new generation of people to go and take the land for Him.

00:04:18.939 --> 00:04:27.515
And that's the kind of people that have the bulldog mentality that go after it like a dog on a bone and say, 'You know what?

00:04:27.515 --> 00:04:29.720
I'm fighting and contending for what's mine.

00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:40.093
' And the Lord told me, 'For what I've called you to do, everything that I have, it's not a victim mentality that gets you there.

00:04:42.205 --> 00:04:45.080
You have a victor mentality, a winner mentality, but a winner mentality contends.

00:04:53.872 --> 00:04:58.280
They fight for it; they say, "This is mine.

00:04:58.280 --> 00:05:00.200
"' Do you understand what I'm saying?

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:12.390
It has to be that: how bad do you want it in these end times with all the stuff that's going on around us.

00:05:14.286 --> 00:05:16.431
There's so much every single day, ladies and gentlemen.

00:05:16.431 --> 00:05:19.794
I just go, 'My goodness, this has been incredible.

00:05:19.794 --> 00:05:24.024
' Even look at what we stopped, I believe, with the Atlanta shooting.

00:05:24.024 --> 00:05:35.269
The guy went in saying he wanted to do something at the airport, had 27 shots and a firearm.

00:05:42.580 --> 00:05:52.120
He walked into the airport, but his family told on him and he was brought to justice by the police department there.

00:05:52.120 --> 00:05:55.553
Thank God that's an answer to prayer.

00:05:55.553 --> 00:05:58.440
That right there shows we're contending.

00:06:03.920 --> 00:06:04.320
We're fighting.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:24.453
We're saying, 'No, you're not going to do this to our airports.

00:06:24.453 --> 00:06:37.966
' Because bottom line, ladies and gentlemen, we wrestle not against flesh and blood; we're wrestling against principalities and powers and spiritual wickedness in high places.

00:06:37.966 --> 00:06:42.013
This was a principality working through a personality.

00:06:42.013 --> 00:06:48.192
But I believe as we are praying believers that come in agreement and intercede for our nation, we're stopping this stuff.

00:07:00.360 --> 00:07:00.630
Now, I believe there's a lot more to stop.

00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:10.920
But praying for our economy to turn around—there are so many people saying we're in a recession.

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:24.200
There are so many people saying that it's worse than 2008, that it's going to get worse than that and go into the Great Depression.

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:25.942
And I said, 'Not yet.

00:07:25.942 --> 00:07:39.440
' So that's why I wanted you to come on here and pray with me tonight to pray over our economy so that we have that window.

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:59.423
Now, I know I've heard other people say they believe a great economic crisis worse than 2008 will come in the next year, but I believe in God for a supernatural wealth transfer for the body of Christ before all this starts to take place.

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:06.827
I told you I saw President Trump treading the river.

00:08:06.827 --> 00:08:14.698
It was like Niagara Falls, and he was paddling as fast as he could because the boat was going to go over.

00:08:19.027 --> 00:08:30.480
But he was keeping the economy from going clear over by paddling in that canoe as fast as he could because he knew that it was just a matter of time and it was going over.

00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:33.120
It's going into the beast system.

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:35.171
That's where all this is headed.

00:08:37.405 --> 00:08:43.200
We all know that a one-world government, a one-world financial system is coming because that's what the Bible says.

00:08:48.680 --> 00:08:48.900
And so if that's coming, we're not going to stop it.

00:08:48.900 --> 00:08:53.069
Can we delay it and give us more time?

00:08:53.069 --> 00:08:53.606
Yes.

00:08:53.606 --> 00:09:00.333
I believe with our prayers and as we intercede, we're the salt and the light of this world.

00:09:00.333 --> 00:09:10.045
I believe that God has given us the ability to change a lot of things through prayer—delaying things, doing things.

00:09:22.844 --> 00:09:23.129
But I'm going to tell you, we're running out of time.

00:09:23.129 --> 00:09:24.551
Jesus Christ is coming.

00:09:24.551 --> 00:09:36.460
Now, I heard another man this week say, 'We're so far away from all that.

00:09:36.460 --> 00:09:40.194
Don't worry, Jesus isn't coming right now.

00:09:40.194 --> 00:09:55.760
' I don't doubt that we have a lot to do, but I'm going to tell you this: the time clock is ticking and we are at the midnight hour.

00:09:55.760 --> 00:09:59.432
I'm telling you, it's time to wake up.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:16.120
And that's why I've tried to warn you over and over, even at the prayer conference, trying to warn the people that a major shaking is about to take place in this earth to awaken it.

00:10:21.754 --> 00:10:22.211
It's not just about America.

00:10:22.211 --> 00:10:34.514
President Trump said today, 'Well, we have over 17 trillion dollars worth of stuff coming in.

00:10:34.514 --> 00:10:44.040
' I don't know where he's getting his numbers, but I pray that's true.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:46.840
I want an economic boom.

00:11:08.533 --> 00:11:08.738
I told you I saw the wave and it was transparent.

00:11:08.738 --> 00:11:12.538
You could see crypto, gold, silver, and the housing market through this.

00:11:25.805 --> 00:11:26.190
That means it was shallow.

00:11:40.865 --> 00:11:41.070
It wasn't a deep, defined wave, but it was a wave.

00:11:41.070 --> 00:11:44.047
Nevertheless, that's the word I would use.

00:11:45.583 --> 00:11:46.160
On top of the soil was gold.

00:11:46.160 --> 00:11:48.510
Do you all remember that?

00:12:00.049 --> 00:12:00.338
And the Lord said, 'There's enough gold on the layer of what's coming right here.

00:12:00.338 --> 00:12:04.520
' It was thin—not a thick foundation, but a thin one.

00:12:04.520 --> 00:12:06.760
He said, 'Enough to line your pockets, son.

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:13.607
Fill your pockets as quickly as you can for what's about to come because it's not thick, it's thin.

00:12:13.607 --> 00:12:16.664
' And that wave will not last very long.

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:36.754
It's a short-lived wave, but it will provide enough for an end-time wealth transfer for you to get the job done to bring in the harvest.

00:12:36.754 --> 00:12:48.446
It's not going to be long-lived, but it will give you enough time and enough money to get the job done.

00:12:50.514 --> 00:12:53.720
Jesus Christ is coming, and I'm telling you, brush arbor Churches, Woodstock Church—it's like Woodstock, Holy Ghost Woodstock.

00:12:53.720 --> 00:12:57.815
All this is coming; it's right at our door.

00:12:57.815 --> 00:13:05.440
But I've tried to tell some of the people, I said, 'We've got to have the money to get it done.

00:13:05.440 --> 00:13:17.840
' It costs millions and millions, if not hundreds of millions and tens of millions of dollars to get the gospel out.

00:13:23.680 --> 00:13:24.000
It's not free: TV time, radio time, all those kinds of things.

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:38.805
The only thing that is free is these YouTubes; they've provided a platform for us to use that we can broadcast like this, and we get thousands of people watching on here, and it doesn't cost anyone anything.

00:13:38.805 --> 00:13:43.040
They just click on their internet provider and watch us on their phone or their tablet.

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:50.440
Most people watch from their tablet or from their television, and some on phones.

00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:52.342
Which is it most, Braden?

00:13:52.342 --> 00:13:53.160
Phone and TV.

00:13:53.160 --> 00:13:54.933
I think it's pretty cool.

00:13:58.714 --> 00:13:59.051
And that's not TV time.

00:13:59.051 --> 00:14:07.845
We're using their platform, but they can turn us off anytime they want to.

00:14:07.845 --> 00:14:09.505
It's their platform.

00:14:09.505 --> 00:14:13.040
That's the part that's shaky.

00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:23.749
The moment we say something against what they believe or what they think, you're done.

00:14:28.568 --> 00:14:31.326
But I believe that persecution is not here yet to the point of where I believe it's coming.

00:14:38.663 --> 00:14:39.640
I told you it would be like an olive press in the days ahead, and the oil will come forth.

00:14:39.640 --> 00:14:41.500
Great persecution is coming on the church.

00:14:41.500 --> 00:14:47.769
And the Lord told me, 'The great harvest will come out of birthing pains.

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:53.550
It will come out of a time of trials because people are not awake.

00:14:53.550 --> 00:14:54.746
People are not alert.

00:14:54.746 --> 00:15:00.920
They're not looking for the coming of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:16.360
' Many people are just like, 'I've heard it so much I don't believe it anymore, really.

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:25.160
' There's a remnant of us who do, and those are the ones I believe are coming on here praying every single time we start prayer, and you're excited about it.

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:30.020
Hey, this is a cool book: In Him by Kenneth E.

00:15:30.020 --> 00:15:30.630
Hagin.

00:15:30.630 --> 00:15:33.035
It's a little short read; it's 32 pages.

00:15:33.035 --> 00:15:34.630
I bet it's less than a dollar.

00:15:35.905 --> 00:15:41.453
You probably can get it for like 25 or 50 cents, I don't know, whatever.

00:15:41.453 --> 00:15:45.640
But it's a good read: In Him by Kenneth E.

00:15:45.640 --> 00:15:46.029
Hagin.

00:15:46.029 --> 00:15:48.280
Little short book, 32 pages.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:50.600
Pretty cool, huh?

00:15:50.871 --> 00:15:53.1000
I like stuff like that; it's like a little pocketbook.

00:15:53.1000 --> 00:15:55.680
Diana found that for me.

00:16:07.476 --> 00:16:07.671
I told her, 'Thanks, baby.

00:16:07.671 --> 00:16:15.360
' She got that and said, 'Hey, Brandon, I think you need to read this: In Him.

00:16:15.360 --> 00:16:23.000
' I have some more over there.

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:29.507
Braden, will you get those other two little books mama got me over there?

00:16:32.831 --> 00:16:34.360
If Diana was here, she could read this to you in less than five minutes.

00:16:34.360 --> 00:16:35.560
She's a fast reader.

00:16:35.560 --> 00:16:41.500
Oh, she got me this one: The Precious Blood of Jesus by Kenneth E.

00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:41.940
Hagin.

00:16:44.520 --> 00:16:47.351
And then she got me The Gifts of Prophecy by Kenneth E.

00:16:47.351 --> 00:16:48.160
Hagin.

00:16:49.959 --> 00:16:52.235
And then she got me Praying to Get Results by Kenneth Hagin.

00:16:52.235 --> 00:16:53.840
They're all short reads.

00:16:53.840 --> 00:16:58.440
She gets me things that don't overwhelm me because I don't like to read that much anyway.

00:16:58.440 --> 00:17:02.257
But it has 71 pages in that one.

00:17:02.257 --> 00:17:06.120
So, it's a pretty cool little book she got me.

00:17:06.120 --> 00:17:12.813
It came in the mail; she got it from Amazon, I guess.

00:17:12.813 --> 00:17:18.359
She surprised me and said, 'Hey, I got that for you tonight.

00:17:18.359 --> 00:17:20.627
Look what I got you, Braden—Brandon.

00:17:20.627 --> 00:17:23.027
' So I'll share with Brent, my son.

00:17:23.027 --> 00:17:25.569
He can read one, and I'll read one a day.

00:17:25.569 --> 00:17:27.031
It keeps you stirred up.

00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:28.329
You have to fan that flame.

00:17:38.930 --> 00:17:39.360
You cannot let your flame go down in these last days.

00:17:40.110 --> 00:17:41.360
You have to stir yourself up.

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:44.520
And that's what I'm trying to tell you.

00:17:46.034 --> 00:17:47.408
This is how I do it.

00:17:51.620 --> 00:17:52.000
This is how Diana does it.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:18:01.867
She'll read one of these little books, she'll drive around and say, 'Let's read that,' finding things to keep yourself stirred up in these last days.

00:18:05.987 --> 00:18:07.013
Don't wait on your pastor to feed you.

00:18:20.971 --> 00:18:26.564
Don't wait on the evangelist to feed you.

00:18:26.564 --> 00:18:28.745
Don't wait on a prophet to feed you.

00:18:28.745 --> 00:18:31.200
Don't wait on YouTube to feed you.

00:18:37.980 --> 00:18:38.130
You have to be a scavenger.

00:18:52.120 --> 00:18:52.312
How badly do you want your life to change?

00:18:52.312 --> 00:18:54.040
How desperate are you to find stuff?

00:18:54.040 --> 00:18:56.679
That's why we're always looking for stuff.

00:18:56.679 --> 00:19:04.000
My goodness, if I waited on my pastors to feed me only, you would die spiritually.

00:19:16.839 --> 00:19:17.279
Do you understand?

00:19:17.279 --> 00:19:21.028
You can't wait on people.

00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:25.080
You have to be a contender.

00:19:25.080 --> 00:19:28.194
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I'm putting my closers in.

00:19:28.194 --> 00:19:34.429
' He said, 'I've saved the best for last—my closers.

00:19:34.429 --> 00:19:39.507
' Diana and I started doing research on the closers; they are built for pressure.

00:19:39.507 --> 00:19:45.114
Closers in baseball—the ones that close the baseball game—are built for pressure.

00:19:49.503 --> 00:19:50.029
They don't lose the lead because they're not going, 'Oh gosh.

00:19:50.029 --> 00:20:02.360
' You know about buck fever when you're hunters and you're out there and your hands are shaking from the pressure of the buck walking in front of you.

00:20:13.990 --> 00:20:14.255
You miss the shot because you've got buck fever.

00:20:32.086 --> 00:20:32.400
That's where we are in these end times.

00:20:32.400 --> 00:20:34.240
God made us for pressure.

00:20:35.351 --> 00:20:39.680
He said, 'Brandon, we've got this, but you've got to be a contender.

00:20:41.373 --> 00:20:47.975
You can't just sit there and lay down on the job and say, "Stop.

00:20:47.975 --> 00:20:51.624
"' Nobody feels sorry for you.

00:20:54.110 --> 00:20:54.800
That's what the Lord said.

00:20:54.800 --> 00:20:56.800
Nobody feels sorry for you.

00:20:56.800 --> 00:20:58.240
Do you understand?

00:20:58.240 --> 00:21:05.640
You've got to play the world's smallest violin for yourself?

00:21:05.640 --> 00:21:07.680
'You had a hard day.

00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:09.160
The enemy was attacking.

00:21:09.160 --> 00:21:11.070
' Stand up and fight.

00:21:17.450 --> 00:21:17.915
Be a contender.

00:21:17.915 --> 00:21:22.400
Say, 'No, I'm not going to let you do this.

00:21:31.217 --> 00:21:31.846
I'm not going to let you rob my family of finances.

00:21:31.846 --> 00:21:36.457
I'm not going to let you rob me of health.

00:21:36.457 --> 00:21:43.570
I'm not going to sit here and have a snotty nose and have all this going on with me.

00:21:43.570 --> 00:21:45.320
I refuse to do this.

00:21:53.684 --> 00:21:54.000
I have a covenant with God.

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:56.423
' You either are or you aren't.

00:21:56.423 --> 00:21:59.547
Are you a believing believer or not?

00:21:59.547 --> 00:22:07.774
Are we believing believers in these last days or are we not?

00:22:07.774 --> 00:22:11.280
That's why I started saying, 'I'm done with this.

00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:15.885
' When you say you're barely getting by, or you're done not feeling good...

00:22:15.885 --> 00:22:17.065
'Oh, you're overweight.

00:22:17.065 --> 00:22:19.751
' Well, you eat too much.

00:22:19.751 --> 00:22:21.280
I work on myself daily.

00:22:21.280 --> 00:22:23.090
'Well, you feel sorry for yourself.

00:22:23.090 --> 00:22:27.938
' No, you're the one that put the food in there.

00:22:27.938 --> 00:22:42.567
You've got one hole; you don't have to keep putting food in it all day long.

00:22:50.891 --> 00:22:51.189
The Lord gets on me about a lot of stuff.

00:22:51.189 --> 00:22:58.453
I walk a very tightrope with the Father.

00:22:58.453 --> 00:23:08.311
He's instructed me on what I'm supposed to be doing with my life, telling me, 'This is how you get there.

00:23:08.311 --> 00:23:33.864
' He always said, 'Brandon, if you want change in your life, you're going to have to change the way you're doing things because you can't keep doing the same thing expecting different results.

00:23:33.864 --> 00:23:43.664
How badly do you want to go on with me?

00:23:59.120 --> 00:23:59.448
How badly do you want this?

00:23:59.448 --> 00:24:02.400
' You want impartation from these generals?

00:24:07.160 --> 00:24:07.500
You want impartation, but are you a contender for it?

00:24:07.500 --> 00:24:18.895
Do you do what they did to get it—from Billy Burke to Lynne Hammond to whoever you know has been in ministry for 50 or 60 years?

00:24:18.895 --> 00:24:22.893
Do you do what they did to get where they are?

00:24:22.893 --> 00:24:29.607
They've sustained it and they've been there.

00:24:46.367 --> 00:24:46.600
Or do you just sit there and go, "Well, you know, there's a reason why there's not very many of them.

00:24:46.600 --> 00:24:49.320
" Nobody said it would be easy, but how bad do you want it?

00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:08.578
And that's why I thought about it.

00:25:23.540 --> 00:25:23.720
You know, there's only one Bill Gates.

00:25:23.720 --> 00:25:29.208
There's only one Warren Buffett.

00:25:29.208 --> 00:25:30.845
There's only one Elon Musk.

00:25:30.845 --> 00:25:37.206
I'm just talking about the wealthiest of the wealthiest.

00:25:37.206 --> 00:25:38.834
But they did something.

00:25:38.834 --> 00:25:57.870
And I'm not saying they did righteous things to get there, but I'm talking about people who contend for the greater wealth.

00:25:57.880 --> 00:25:59.215
It's a pattern.

00:25:59.215 --> 00:26:00.440
They have a different mindset.

00:26:00.440 --> 00:26:01.608
They think differently.

00:26:01.608 --> 00:26:03.068
They don't think poverty.

00:26:03.068 --> 00:26:04.320
They don't think quit.

00:26:04.320 --> 00:26:05.760
They don't think loser.

00:26:05.760 --> 00:26:07.200
They think winner.

00:26:07.200 --> 00:26:15.764
It's like when they say you could retire and never have to work again, "Elon, you're worth $500 million.

00:26:15.764 --> 00:26:18.053
